                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1168: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-17T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 17, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>450. Legation’s 439, June 13, 3 p.m. The following telegram from the American
                    Consul General at Hankow is being repeated to the Minister at Nanking: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“June 15, 1 p.m. Inasmuch as the Americans resident at Kanchow and in
                            that vicinity have more than once been advised to withdraw to a zone of
                            safety I can offer no further suggestion as a possible means of relief
                            except that it might be advisable to continue to urge the Nanking
                            authorities to supply adequate forces for the protection of American
                            life and property in the Kanchow area. So far as can be ascertained
                            Chang Fah-kwei does not appear to be making any headway towards either
                            Nanchang or Hankow at present.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
